    "*** You have a standard deck of 52 playing cards. There are two colors (black and red) and four suits (spades are black, clubs are black, hearts are red, and diamonds are red). Each suit has 13 cards, in which there is an ace, numbered cards from 2 to 10, and three face cards (jack, queen, and king).***\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "*** a. You randomly draw and then replace a card. What’s the probability it’s an ace? What’s the probability it’s the 4 of spades?***\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Probability of an ace: 4/52 = 1/13\n",
    "\n",
    "Probability of 4 of spades: 1/52"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "*** b. You randomly draw a card, and after replacing it, you draw another. Let A be the event that the card is a club; let B be the event that the card is red. What is Pr(A|B)? That is, what is the probability the second card is a club, given the first one was a red card? Are the two events independent? ***\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "P(A|B) = 13/52 = 1/4 \n",
    "\n",
    "P(A) = 13/52 = 1/4\n",
    "\n",
    "P(A|B) = P(A) => Two events independent\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "*** c. Repeat (b), this time assuming that when the first (club) card is drawn, it is not replaced. Would this change your answer to (b) in terms of independence? ***\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "P(A|B) = 13/51\n",
    "\n",
    "P(A) = 13/52\n",
    "\n",
    "=> Two events are not independent"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "*** d. Let C be the event a card is a face card, and let D be the event a card is black. You draw a single card. Evaluate Pr(C ∩ D). Are the two events mutually exclusive? ***"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "P(C) = 12/52\n",
    "\n",
    "P(D) = 13/52\n",
    "\n",
    "P(C ∩ D) = P(C|D) × P(D) = 3/13 * 13/52 = 3/52\n",
    "\n",
    "P(C) * P(D) = 12/52 * 13/52 = 3/52\n",
    "\n",
    "Two events are mutually exclusive \n"
   ]
